 This is a bug."}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 3, "created_at": "2016-05-29T23:36:10Z", "updated_at": "2020-12-08T02:06:29Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "```\nfn main() {\n    macro_rules! a {\n        ($e:expr) => { $e; }\n    }\n    a!(true)\n}\n```\n\nError: Expected `()`, found `bool`\n\nBut:\n\n```\nfn main() {\n    macro_rules! a {\n        ($e:expr) => { $e; }\n    }\n    a!(true);  // <-- semicolon\n}\n```\n\ndoes not warn that the `;` is ignored.\n\nSo either\n- there should be a warning that the `;` has no effect in the macro, or\n- the `;` inside the macro should turn the expression into `()`.\n", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/33953/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/33953/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}